                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.802 Lloyd Brasileiro Navigation Co./27:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-16T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 16, 1931—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. Your 24, April 29, 3 p.m. The Department feels that Article 7 of decree
                    19682, by granting reduction in fees to shippers by Lloyd Brasileiro line, in
                    effect discriminates directly against competing American lines and is thus
                    contrary to the general principle of flag treatment of foreign vessels usually
                    observed by maritime nations. It therefore wishes you informally to present this
                    point of view to appropriate Brazilian authorities and make further effort to
                    secure modification of decree.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
